column4:
You have heard that it was said, `An eye for an eye and a tooth for a tooth.'
Matthäus,5,39,But I say to you, Do not resist one who is evil. But if any one strikes you on the right cheek, turn to him the other also;
Matthäus,5,40,and if any one would sue you and take your coat, let him have your cloak as well;
Matthäus,5,41,and if any one forces you to go one mile, go with him two miles.
Matthäus,5,42,Give to him who begs from you, and do not refuse him who would borrow from you.
Matthäus,5,43,You have heard that it was said

The eye is the lamp of the body. So, if your eye is sound, your whole body will be full of light;
Matthäus,6,23,but if your eye is not sound, your whole body will be full of darkness. If then the light in you is darkness, how great is the darkness!
Matthäus,6,24,No one can serve two masters; for either he will hate the one and love the other

Every one then who hears these words of mine and does them will be like a wise man who built his house upon the rock;
Matthäus,7,25,and the rain fell, and the floods came, and the winds blew and beat upon that house, but it did not fall, because it had been founded on the rock.
Matthäus,7,26,And every one who hears these words of mine and does not do them will be like a foolish man who built his house upon the sand;
Matthäus,7,27,and the rain fell, and the floods came, and the winds blew and beat against that house, and it fell; and great was the fall of it.

Behold, my servant whom I have chosen, my beloved with whom my soul is well pleased. I will put my Spirit upon him, and he shall proclaim justice to the Gentiles.
Matthäus,12,19,He will not wrangle or cry aloud, nor will any one hear his voice in the streets;
Matthäus,12,20,he will not break a bruised reed or quench a smoldering wick, till he brings justice to victory;
Matthäus,12,21,and in his name will the Gentiles hope.

Whoever receives one such child in my name receives me;
Matthäus,18,6,but whoever causes one of these little ones who believe in me to sin, it would be better for him to have a great millstone fastened round his neck and to be drowned in the depth of the sea.
Matthäus,18,7,Woe to the world for temptations to sin! For it is necessary that temptations come

Immediately after the tribulation of those days the sun will be darkened, and the moon will not give its light, and the stars will fall from heaven, and the powers of the heavens will be shaken;
Matthäus,24,30,then will appear the sign of the Son of man in heaven, and then all the tribes of the earth will mourn, and they will see the Son of man coming on the clouds of heaven with power and great glory;
Matthäus,24,31,and he will send out his angels with a loud trumpet call, and they will gather his elect from the four winds, from one end of heaven to the other.
Matthäus,24,32,From the fig tree learn its lesson: as soon as its branch becomes tender and puts forth its leaves

Teacher, Moses wrote for us that if a man's brother dies and leaves a wife, but leaves no child, the man must take the wife, and raise up children for his brother.
Markus,12,20,There were seven brothers; the first took a wife, and when he died left no children;
Markus,12,21,and the second took her, and died, leaving no children; and the third likewise;
Markus,12,22,and the seven left no children. Last of all the woman also died.
Markus,12,23,In the resurrection whose wife will she be? For the seven had her as wife.

I came to cast fire upon the earth; and would that it were already kindled!
Lukas,12,50,I have a baptism to be baptized with; and how I am constrained until it is accomplished!
Lukas,12,51,Do you think that I have come to give peace on earth? No, I tell you, but rather division;
Lukas,12,52,for henceforth in one house there will be five divided, three against two and two against three;
Lukas,12,53,they will be divided, father against son and son against father, mother against daughter and daughter against her mother, mother-in-law against her daughter-in-law and daughter-in-law against her mother-in-law.

But when you see Jerusalem surrounded by armies, then know that its desolation has come near.
Lukas,21,21,Then let those who are in Judea flee to the mountains, and let those who are inside the city depart, and let not those who are out in the country enter it;
Lukas,21,22,for these are days of vengeance, to fulfil all that is written.
Lukas,21,23,Alas for those who are with child and for those who give suck in those days! For great distress shall be upon the earth and wrath upon this people;
Lukas,21,24,they will fall by the edge of the sword, and be led captive among all nations; and Jerusalem will be trodden down by the Gentiles, until the times of the Gentiles are fulfilled.
Lukas,21,25,And there will be signs in sun and moon and stars

But take heed to yourselves lest your hearts be weighed down with dissipation and drunkenness and cares of this life, and that day come upon you suddenly like a snare;
Lukas,21,35,for it will come upon all who dwell upon the face of the whole earth.
Lukas,21,36,But watch at all times, praying that you may have strength to escape all these things that will take place, and to stand before the Son of man.

Men, why are you doing this? We also are men, of like nature with you, and bring you good news, that you should turn from these vain things to a living God who made the heaven and the earth and the sea and all that is in them.
Apostelgeschichte,14,16,In past generations he allowed all the nations to walk in their own ways;
Apostelgeschichte,14,17,yet he did not leave himself without witness, for he did good and gave you from heaven rains and fruitful seasons, satisfying your hearts with food and gladness.
